rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A private company that provides local bus or limousine transportation to and from airports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airport Shuttle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A railway that transports automobiles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car railway

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all bridges. Bridges are the structures built to span water, valleys, roads, or other physical obstacles with the goal of providing passage over the obstacle. See also mso:transportation.bridge_type for the collection of types of bridges.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bridge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a bridge to the body of water that is straddled by the bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Body of Water

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a bridge to a descriptor for the style of the bridge, e.g. arch bridge, truss bridge, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bridge Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a bridge to the height from the water line to the lowest part of the bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clearance Below

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.bridge to the maximum amount of weight that the bridge can bear at a given time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Load

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a bridge to one of the land masses that is connected by the bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locale

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a bridge to the greatest distance in meters between two intermediate supports that are not separated by another intermediate support.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest Span

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a bridge to the total number of segments between intermediate supports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of spans

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:transportation.bridge to the number of piers standing in water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Piers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating mso:transportation.bridge to the physical object the bridge spans.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spans

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The length in meters of the given bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The width in meters of the given bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for styles of bridges, e.g. arch bridge, truss bridge, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bridge Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking a bridge-style descriptor with a particular bridge that instantiates this style.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bridges

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A transportation structure where a bus line that is part of a mass transit network for a metropolitan area stops to pick up and drop off passengers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bus Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An engineered waterway that is used for transportation or irrigation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Canal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a canal to the maximum length of boats that are permitted to use the canal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Boat Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a canal to the maximum width (beam) of boats that are permitted to use the canal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Boat Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a canal to a number indicating how many locks the canal contains.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Locks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in providing a rented car (without a chauffeur or hired driver).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car Rental Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a car rental service with an action of booking a rental car through the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reserve Car

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A private company that allows groups and organizations to contract buses with drivers for special events.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Charter Bus Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A route used by a boat or other watercraft to transport people and/or vehicles across a body of water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ferry Route

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure and associated facilities where a ferry boat docks and where passengers, automobiles, and/or cargo can embark or disembark.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ferry Terminal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure where gliders (fixed wing aircraft without a source of power) can land and depart.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Glider Port

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure where helicopters can both land and take flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heliport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A network of high-speed roads, e.g. the National Highway System of the United States.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Highway System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a highway system to one of the roads that make up the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Highways

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in providing a rented car which includes a chauffeur (hired driver). Note that a hired car service differs from a taxi service in that taxis typically include a meter and can be hailed from the street.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hired Car Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a hired-car service to the fixed, initial charge for using the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Base Charge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a hired-car service to the charge, if there is one, of cancelling a reservation with the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cancellation Charge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a hired-car service to the cost per mile, if fares are assessed on this basis, to use the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cost per Mile

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a hired-car service to the cost per minute, if fares are assessed on this basis, to use the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cost per Minute

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a hired-car service to the minimum total charge for using the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Charge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a hired-car service to the surcharge, expressed as a percentage, by which the service increases fares during times with heavy traffic, e.g. rush hour.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Primetime Surcharge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a hired-car service to a reservation that is made with the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reservation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure where hot air balloons can land and depart.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hot Air Balloon Port

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all marine terminals. These are the locations within a port with at least one berth or wharf, optionally with equipment to handle cargo loading/unloading, ship repair and refueling, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Marine Terminal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.marine_terminal to the total length of the terminal's berth area. Also called total dock length.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Berth Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.marine_terminal to the maximum crane lift capacity available at the Terminal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Crane Lift Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.marine_terminal to the number of berths, or wharfs, at the terminal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Berths

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.marine_terminal to the services the terminal provides to ships.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Services

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A place where urban rapid transit trains pick up and drop off passengers, often underground or elevated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Metro Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A marker that is set up on a road to indicate how far the marker is from the beginning of the road.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Milepost

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a milepost to a measure, in kilometers, indicating how far the milepost is from the beginning of the road.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a milepost to the road along which the milepost is placed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Road

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all park and ride structures. Park and ride are those places commuters can park personal vehicles and catch public transportation vehicles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Park and Ride

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of ports. Ports are locations on a coast with harbors where ships can dock and transfer passengers and cargo to and from land.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Port

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a port to the maximum size of vessels, in terms of the distance between the waterline and the highest point on the vessel, that can be accommodated by the port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Air Draft

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the number of cargo vessels serviced in a given year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Annual Cargo Vessels

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the amount of container volume in Twenty Foot Equivalent units for a given year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Annual Container Volume (TEU)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the total amount of cargo in metric tonnes that passes through the port in a given year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Annual Tonnage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a port to the total value of goods that pass through the port in a given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cargo Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a port to the the maximum size of vessels, in terms of the distance between the waterline and the bottom of the hull, that can be accommodated by the port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Draft Depth

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a port to the harbor where the port is located.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Harbor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the type of harbor where the port is located.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Harbor Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to a mso:transportation.marine_terminal that is located at the port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Marine Terminal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the number of berths available at the port. Berths are the designated areas at a dock that a ship parks at, or berths, for cargo transfer, break bulk operations, marine transfer operations, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Berths

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the number of annual docked vessels. This number includes containers, tankers, ferries, cruise passenger, bulk carriers, barges and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Docked Vessels

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a port to the number of piers at the port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Piers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a port to the number of wharves at the port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Wharves

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.port to the total length of berth available at the port. A berth is a designated location within a port for mooring vessels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Berth Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all port services. These are the services the mso:transportation.port provides to incoming and outgoing vessels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Port Services

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A network of twin steel-rail tracks which is used to route trains from one location to another.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure where a train line that is part of a mass transit network for a metropolitan area, e.g. a streetcar or light rail line, stops to pick up and drop off passengers. Note that mso:rail.railway_terminus should be used for train stations that travel outside of a single metropolitan area.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railroad Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A designated area, usually along a major highway, where motorists can take a break from driving or riding in their automobiles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rest Area

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A road is a route used for land transport and along which motor vehicles can be driven. This type includes both paved and unpaved roads.
Things that are a road:
## Highways and freeways (e.g. Mexican Federal Highway, M56 Lena Highway).
## Avenues (e.g. Epifanio de los Santos Avenue, Moi Avenue, Alexandras Avenue).
## Streets (e.g. Nevsky Prospekt, Fleet Street, Stanley Street).
## Toll roads and turnpikes (e.g. Florida???s Turnpike, Will Rogers Turnpike, Cipularang Toll Road).
## Restricted and/or limited-access roads such as private roads and government-owned roads.
Things that are NOT a road:
## Highway systems (e.g. Autostrade of Italy, China National Highways, US numbered highways). Use mso:transportation.highway_system in these cases.
## Pedestrian paths such as footpaths, walkways and hiking trails (e.g. Australian Alps Walking Track, Wicklow Way, Legaran Segget). Use mso:transportation.trail for these.
## Bridges (e.g. Luzhniki Metro Bridge, Oland Bridge, Akashi-Kaikyo Bridge). Use mso:transportation.bridge for these.
## Tunnels (e.g. Eiksund Tunnel, Honningsv??g Tunnel, L??rdalstunnelen). Use mso:transportation.tunnel for these.
## Taxiways and airport runways.
## Railroads and railways (e.g. Mont Alto Rail Road, Danube Valley Railway, Alderney Railway). Use mso:rail.railway for these.
## Dedicated tracks for guided buses (e.g. Cambridgeshire Guided Busway, O-Bahn Busway).
## Race tracks (e.g. Valencia Street Circuit, Singapore Street Circuit, Bahrain International Circuit). Use mso:sports.race_track for these.
## Locations that have "road" in their names but refer to harbors and anchorages (e.g. Royal Roads, Lahaina Roads, Hampton Roads).

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A linear segment of a route upon which vehicles, pedestrians, and/or materials can move.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Routable Structure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a routable structure to the location where the structure begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Begins

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:transportation.routable_structure to a descriptor of the type of things that move along the structure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Carries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a routable structure to a direction in which the structure runs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Direction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a routable structure to the location where the structure ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ends

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.routable_structure to the amount of toll paid and the time during which the toll was valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Toll

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure where seaplanes can land and depart. A seaplane is a fixed-wing aircraft that can alight on and take off from a body of water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Seaplane Base

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure comprised of ticket offices, platforms, and other facilities for loading and unloading subway passengers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subway Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in providing transportation via a rented car with a chauffeur. Note that a taxi service differs from a hired-car service in that taxis typically include a meter and can be hailed from the street.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Taxi Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all taxi stands. These are the areas on a street or near a structure where taxis queue to wait for passengers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Taxicab Stand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An installation which collects a fee for the use of a road or some other transportation structure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Toll Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type used to collect information about the flow of traffic through a particular road segment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Flow

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The end of the time frame corresponding to the traffic flow information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Flow End Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The average number of seconds required to traverse the HOV (high occupancy vehicle) lane(s) of the road segment in the given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: HOV Delay

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The average number of seconds required to traverse the road segment in regular lanes in the given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overall Delay

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The road segment relating to the traffic flow information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Road Segment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The status of the road segment for which information is provided, e.g. whether the road segment is open, closed, impassible, congested, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Road Segment Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The beginning of the time frame corresponding to the traffic flow information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Flow Start Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A discrete event that significantly disturbs the flow of traffic, e.g. a traffic accident.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The latitude measurement where the traffic incident ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident End Latitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The longitude measurement where the traffic incident ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident End Longitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The end of the time frame corresponding to the traffic incident.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident End Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The latitude measurement where the traffic incident begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident Start Latitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The longitude measurement where the traffic incident begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident Start Longitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The beginning of the time frame corresponding to the traffic incident.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident Start Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A specification of the status of the traffic incident, e.g. reported or confirmed. This can be from a coded scheme or it can be an unnormalized text string.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A description of the traffic incident in a Traffic Message Channel code, which specifies the event type, the location, the expected duration of the incident etc. in a coded format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Message Channel Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Traffic flow information relating to the given traffic incident.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of traffic incident, e.g. accident, disabled vehicle, planned event, etc. This can be from a coded scheme or it can be an unnormalized text string.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic Incident Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A path, track, or route used by pedestrians, animals, or off-road vehicles
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trail

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type of activity that is associated with the trail, e.g. hiking, biking, running, fishing, hunting, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trail Activity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The relative level of difficulty of the trail, e.g. easy, moderate, and expert.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trail Difficulty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The average amount of time that is needed to traverse the trail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Duration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The total increase in elevation that results from traversing the trail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Elevation Gain

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the trail is appropriate for children.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Kid Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A qualitative descriptor of the relative length of the trail, e.g. short, intermediate, and long.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The location of the trail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A trail that is within a small radius from the given trail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nearby Trail

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the trail is appropriate for pets, especially dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pet Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a trail to information about the popularity of the trail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trail Popularity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A season of the year when use of the trail is recommended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recommended Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A descriptor for the type of trail, e.g. rail trail, multiple points, loop, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trail Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.trail to the mso:location.location that is the trailhead, a place to access the trail, or in point-to-point trails the 'beginning' of the trail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trailhead

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all trail types. These are the groupings of trails that describe the type of trail, like 'loop' or 'point to point'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trail Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that the system had this length.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The length of the system in kilometers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that provides local transportation services.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Transportation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a transportation service to an action of making a reservation with the transportation service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reservation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure that is used for transportation purposes, e.g. a bus station, a railway or a road.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Transportation Structure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.transportation_structure to the mso:measurement_unit.dated_float containing the number of passengers using the structure and the date the number is valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passenger Usage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.transportation_structure to the maximum height of vehicles in meters that can use the structure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Clearance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:transportation.transportation_structure to the average number of vehicles that pass through the structure on a daily basis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Traffic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A subterranean passageway for vehicles or pedestrians.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tunnel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structure where ultralight fixed-wing aircraft can land and depart. An ultralight weighs less than 1,000 pounds and has a maximum stalling speed of 40 miles per hour.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ultralight Aircraft Port
